description: Reserved matters submission seeking approval of Access, Layout, Scale, Appearance and Landscaping for Phase One of the regeneration of the Eastfields Estate. Phase One will comprise of the demolition of part of the estate comprising of: 63-110 Clay Avenue; 1-60 Pains Close; 1-44 Potter Close; and 1-12 Thrupp Close; and the construction of a series of buildings to provide new homes (use class C3) and ancillary community space; associated communal amenity and play spaces; public open space including flexible games area, outdoor gym facilities and play space; public realm works, including underground refuse stores; car and cycle parking spaces; and associated landscaping, access and highways and utilities works. Phase One will be delivered in sub-phases.
